<item>
            <title>[SOLR-8386] The new admin UI doesn&apos;t understand that managed schemas are the default in 6.0</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-8386</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-8131&quot; title=&quot;Make ManagedIndexSchemaFactory as the default in Solr&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-8131&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-8131&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; makes managed schema the default in Solr 6.0. So the &quot;add field&quot; &amp;amp; etc buttons aren&apos;t being shown in the schema link as they are in 5.x (5.4+).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note, &lt;em&gt;all&lt;/em&gt; the configsets in 5.5+ are managed, as they are in 6.x The difference is that you do not need to specify anything special in 6x. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So whatever the key that determines whether the admin UI knows the schema is managed or not probably needs to be updated.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=upayavira&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;upayavira&quot;&gt;upayavira&lt;/a&gt; any hints here?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12919987">SOLR-8386</key>
            <summary>The new admin UI doesn&apos;t understand that managed schemas are the default in 6.0</summary>
